Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of coverage and rate in co-existing RF and VLC networks, which involves the study of network design parameters, interference, association probability, and user performance. This falls under the domain of network engineering and communication systems, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as it covers the design, analysis, and optimization of communication networks. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as it deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems and their performance analysis. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) covers a broad range of topics related to communication systems and their applications. cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as VLC networks involve the transmission of multimedia content using light waves. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still relevant as it covers the analysis and control of complex systems, which can be applied to network optimization and performance analysis.
